==The Underground Pass==
===Talking to Koftik or attempting to enter the pass===
* '''Player:''' Hello there, you must be Koftik.
* '''Koftik:''' That I am adventurer. King Lathas told me to expect you. I assume he has told you our goal?
* '''Player:''' He said we need to find a way through the Underground Pass. Shouldn't be too bad, I've travelled through many a cave in my time.
* '''Koftik:''' These caves are different... There is a darkness in there unlike any other. You can feel it as you wind your way round the stalagmites... an icy chill that penetrates the very fabric of your being...
* '''Player:''' You've been in before?
* '''Koftik:''' I have. I didn't go far though, nor did I stay for long. People change in these caves...
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I'll take my chances.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll take my chances.
** '''Koftik:''' Okay traveller, I'll catch up with you by the bridge.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Tell me more...}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me more...
** '''Koftik:''' I remember one warrior. His name was Randas. He stood tall and proud like an elven king...
** '''Koftik:''' That same pride made him vulnerable. Randas' worthy desire to be a great and mighty warrior also made him corruptible.
** '''Koftik:''' Within the cave, he heard the voice of Zamorak himself...
** '''Koftik:''' Zamorak showed him a way to achieve his goals by appealing to that most base and dark nature... One that resides in all of us.
** '''Player:''' What happened to him?
** '''Koftik:''' No one knows...
** '''Koftik:''' Anyway, head on in when you're ready. You'll soon come to a bridge, I will catch up with you there.
** {{tact|end}}

